In Arduino, the `int8_t` data type is defined in the `stdint.h` library and it represents an 8-bit signed integer, similar to `int8` in MATLAB. The maximum value that can be stored in an `int8_t` data type in Arduino is 127.

Here is an example code snippet to display the maximum value for `int8_t` data type in Arduino:

```cpp
#include <stdint.h>

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(9600);

  int8_t max_int8_t = 127;

  Serial.print("The maximum value for int8_t in Arduino is: ");
  Serial.println(max_int8_t);
}

void loop() {
  // Do nothing in the loop
}
```

After uploading this code to your Arduino board and opening the Serial Monitor, you will see the message "The maximum value for int8_t in Arduino is: 127" displayed.
